'''Lingbao Tianzun''', also known in [[English language|English]] as the '''Lord of Lingbao''',<ref name=ciic4/> is a [[Taoism|Taoist]] [[god]]. Also known as '''Shangqing''', he is numbered among the [[Three Pure Ones]] who head some forms of the Taoist pantheon.

==Temples==
The [[Dongxuan Palace]] in the [[Zhujia'ao Valley]] beside {{nowrap|[[Mt Mian]]}} in [[Shanxi]] is dedicated to the Lord of Lingbao. His statue in its main hall is covered by a [[Halo (religious iconography)|ring of light]]; his eyes are thought to "contain the mysteries of the universe".<ref name=ciic4>{{harvp|CIIC|2010|p=[http://www.china.org.cn/travel/2010-07/27/content_20582377_4.htm 4]}}.</ref>

